Train Test Split

Ns nunca subimos os dados de treino para o modelo, subimos para 'produo' apenas os dados de teste. Os dados de treino a gente realmente utiliza para treinar o modelo. A proporo entre os dados de treino e de teste variam, mas tem como padro ser:

  • 20% para teste
  • 80% para treino
In[22]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

In[48]:
def plot_incorrect_predictions(df_predictions, x_axis_feature, y_axis_feature):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 10))
    axs = axs.flatten()
    sns.scatterplot(x=x_axis_feature, y=y_axis_feature,
                    hue='Prediction_Label', data=df_predictions, ax=axs[0])
    sns.scatterplot(x=x_axis_feature, y=y_axis_feature,
                    hue='target_name', data=df_predictions, ax=axs[1])
    sns.scatterplot(x=x_axis_feature, y=y_axis_feature,
                    hue='Correct Prediction', data=df_predictions, ax=axs[2])
    axs[3].set_visible(False)

    plt.show()
In[49]:
plot_incorrect_predictions(
    df_predictions, 'petal length (cm)', 'petal width (cm)')

Model Tuning

O que Model Tuning? Model Tuning tentar determinar os parmetros do nosso modelo (tambm conhecidos como hiper parmetros) que maximizam a performance do nosso modelo

In[50]:
for reg_param in (0.1, 0.05, 0.045, 0.04, 0.23, 0.3, 0.9, 1, 1.3, 1.9, 3, 4, 6, 8):
    print(reg_param)
    model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=200, C=reg_param)
    accuracies = cross_val_score(
        model, X_train, y_train, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    print(f"Accuracy: {np.mean(accuracies) * 100:.2f}%")
